01:34:45,011 --> 01:34:47,646
Thumb up my butt sounds better.

1266
01:34:47,681 --> 01:34:51,336
Skeets, come on.
Give me that, you shithead.

1267
01:34:51,351 --> 01:34:53,351
Floyd, come on.

1268
01:34:58,149 --> 01:35:00,954
Will you throw that away, please?

1269
01:35:06,157 --> 01:35:08,157
Well, shit.

1270
01:35:20,547 --> 01:35:23,341
The kid passed. C + average.

1271
01:35:23,550 --> 01:35:25,845
Thought you'd like to know.

1272
01:35:41,902 --> 01:35:43,902
Warden wants to talk.

1273
01:35:57,083 --> 01:35:58,276
Out here?

1274
01:35:58,376 --> 01:36:00,587
That's what the man said.

1275
01:36:16,728 --> 01:36:18,728
Warden?

1276
01:36:27,739 --> 01:36:32,499
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

1277
01:36:33,286 --> 01:36:35,921
I feel awkward enough as it is.

1278
01:36:54,015 --> 01:36:56,101
We got a situation here.

1279
01:36:56,977 --> 01:36:59,171
I think you can appreciate that.

1280
01:36:59,271 --> 01:37:00,672
Yes, sir.

1281
01:37:00,772 --> 01:37:02,340
I sure can.

1282
01:37:02,440 --> 01:37:07,846
I tell you, son, this thing really
came along and knocked my wind out.

1283
01:37:07,946 --> 01:37:11,261
It's got me up nights.
That's the truth.

1284
01:37:12,784 --> 01:37:14,824
The right thing to do...

1285
01:37:16,288 --> 01:37:20,028
...sometimes it's hard to know what that is.

1286
01:37:21,001 --> 01:37:23,001
Do you understand?

1287
01:37:24,754 --> 01:37:26,754
I need your help, son.

1288
01:37:27,799 --> 01:37:30,202
If I'm going to move on this...

1289
01:37:30,302 --> 01:37:34,081
...there can't be
the least little shred of doubt.

1290
01:37:34,181 --> 01:37:35,373
I have to know...

1291
01:37:35,473 --> 01:37:38,210
...if what you told Dufresne was the truth.

1292
01:37:38,310 --> 01:37:39,544
Yes, sir.

1293
01:37:39,644 --> 01:37:41,254
Absolutely.

1294
01:37:41,354 --> 01:37:44,466
Would you be willing to swear
before a judge and jury...

1295
01:37:44,566 --> 01:37:46,676
...with your hand on the Good Book...

1296
01:37:46,776 --> 01:37:49,554
...and take an oath
before Almighty God himself?

1297
01:37:49,654 --> 01:37:51,779
Just give me that chance.

1298
01:37:55,702 --> 01:37:57,702
That's what I thought.

1299
01:38:44,125 --> 01:38:46,590
I'm sure by now you've heard.

1300
01:38:47,796 --> 01:38:49,796
Terrible thing.

1301
01:38:50,423 --> 01:38:52,159
A man that young...

1302
01:38:52,259 --> 01:38:55,287
...less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

1303
01:38:55,387 --> 01:38:58,498
Broke Captain Hadley's heart to shoot him.

1304
01:38:58,598 --> 01:39:00,598
Truly, it did.

1305
01:39:03,103 --> 01:39:05,908
We just have to put it behind us.

1306
01:39:07,232 --> 01:39:09,232
Move on.

1307
01:39:10,068 --> 01:39:12,068
I'm done.

1308
01:39:12,863 --> 01:39:14,863
Everything stops.

1309
01:39:16,449 --> 01:39:19,424
Get someone else to run your scams.

1310
01:39:20,078 --> 01:39:22,078
Nothing stops.

1311
01:39:23,248 --> 01:39:25,248
Nothing.

1312
01:39:27,794 --> 01:39:31,279
Or you will do the hardest time there is.

1313
01:39:31,298 --> 01:39:33,742
No more protection from the guards.

1314
01:39:33,842 --> 01:39:40,040
I'll pull you out of that 1-bunk Hilton
and cast you down with the sodomites.

1315
01:39:40,140 --> 01:39:43,795
You'll think you've been fucked by a train.

1316
01:39:43,977 --> 01:39:45,977
And the library?

1317
01:39:46,146 --> 01:39:47,672
Gone.

1318
01:39:47,772 --> 01:39:50,317
Sealed off, brick by brick.

1319
01:39:50,817 --> 01:39:53,553
We'll have us a little
book barbecue in the yard.

1320
01:39:53,653 --> 01:39:55,889
They'll see the flames for miles.

1321
01:39:55,989 --> 01:39:59,304
We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.

1322
01:40:00,118 --> 01:40:03,263
You understand me? Catching my drift?

1323
01:40:06,833 --> 01:40:08,833
Or am I being obtuse?

1324
01:40:20,514 --> 01:40:23,999
Give him another month to think about it.

1325
01:41:09,896 --> 01:41:13,466
My wife used to say
I'm a hard man to know.

1326
01:41:13,733 --> 01:41:15,733
Like a closed book.

1327
01:41:16,403 --> 01:41:19,208
Complained about it all the time.

1328
01:41:19,364 --> 01:41:21,364
She was beautiful.

1329
01:41:23,326 --> 01:41:25,326
God, I loved her.

1330
01:41:28,582 --> 01:41:32,067
I didn't know how to show it, that's all.

1331
01:41:33,545 --> 01:41:35,545
I killed her, Red.

1332
01:41:37,090 --> 01:41:39,470
I didn't pull the trigger...

1333
01:41:40,302 --> 01:41:42,342
...but I drove her away.

1334
01:41:43,555 --> 01:41:46,333
That's why she died, because of me...

1335
01:41:46,433 --> 01:41:48,433
...the way I am.

1336
01:41:56,818 --> 01:41:59,453
That don't make you a murderer.

1337
01:42:02,032 --> 01:42:04,032
Bad husband, maybe.

1338
01:42:07,454 --> 01:42:10,816
Feel bad about it if you want,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

1339
01:42:10,916 --> 01:42:12,526
No, I didn't.

1340
01:42:12,626 --> 01:42:14,626
Somebody else did.

1341
01:42:15,795 --> 01:42:17,923
And I wound up in here.

1342
01:42:20,383 --> 01:42:22,383
Bad luck, I guess.

1343
01:42:27,182 --> 01:42:29,182
It floats around.

1344
01:42:29,643 --> 01:42:32,108
It's got to land on somebody.

1345
01:42:32,812 --> 01:42:35,107
It was my turn, that's all.

1346
01:42:35,398 --> 01:42:38,203
I was in the path of the tornado.

1347
01:42:44,115 --> 01:42:49,130
I just didn't expect the storm
would last as long as it has.

1348
01:42:52,415 --> 01:42:55,305
Think you'll ever get out of here?

1349
01:42:55,335 --> 01:42:57,335
Me?

1350
01:42:59,339 --> 01:43:01,339
Yeah.

1351
01:43:01,675 --> 01:43:04,077
One day, when I got a long, white beard...

1352
01:43:04,177 --> 01:43:08,512
...and two or three marbles
rolling around upstairs.

1353
01:43:09,391 --> 01:43:11,431
I tell you where I'd go.

1354
01:43:12,519 --> 01:43:14,519
Zihuatanejo.

1355
01:43:15,021 --> 01:43:16,423
Say what?

1356
01:43:16,523 --> 01:43:18,523
Zihuatanejo.

1357
01:43:19,317 --> 01:43:21,317
It's in Mexico.

1358
01:43:22,362 --> 01:43:25,422
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

1359
01:43:25,615 --> 01:43:29,695
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

1360
01:43:30,203 --> 01:43:32,413
They say it has no memory.

1361
01:43:34,207 --> 01:43:38,202
That's where I want to live
the rest of my life.

1362
01:43:38,503 --> 01:43:40,964
A warm place with no memory.

1363
01:43:44,217 --> 01:43:46,342
Open up a little hotel...

1364
01:43:47,888 --> 01:43:49,888
...right on the beach.

1365
01:43:49,973 --> 01:43:52,523
Buy some worthless old boat...

1366
01:43:52,726 --> 01:43:54,726
...and fix it up new.

1367
01:43:57,063 --> 01:43:59,063
Take my guests out...

1368
01:43:59,149 --> 01:44:01,149
...charter fishing.

1369
01:44:04,362 --> 01:44:06,362
Zihuatanejo.

1370
01:44:09,618 --> 01:44:15,398
In a place like that, I could use
a man that knows how to get things.

1371
01:44:20,045 --> 01:44:23,870
I don't think I could make it on the outside.

1372
01:44:29,554 --> 01:44:32,189
I been in here most of my life.

1373
01:44:33,058 --> 01:44:35,523
I'm an institutional man now.

1374
01:44:35,727 --> 01:44:37,727
Just like Brooks was.

1375
01:44:38,939 --> 01:44:41,091
You underestimate yourself.

1376
01:44:41,191 --> 01:44:43,191
I don't think so.

1377
01:44:46,613 --> 01:44:51,226
In here I'm the guy who can get things
for you, sure, but...

1378
01:44:51,326 --> 01:44:53,979
...outside all you need is the Yellow Pages.

1379
01:44:54,079 --> 01:44:57,224
Hell, I wouldn't know where to begin.

1380
01:44:58,458 --> 01:45:00,458
Pacific Ocean?

1381
01:45:00,460 --> 01:45:01,987
Shit.

1382
01:45:02,087 --> 01:45:04,364
Scare me to death,
something that big.

1383
01:45:04,464 --> 01:45:06,464
Not me.

1384
01:45:06,967 --> 01:45:11,387
I didn't shoot my wife,
and I didn't shoot her lover.

1385
01:45:11,471 --> 01:45:15,667
Whatever mistakes I made,
I've paid for them and then some.

1386
01:45:15,767 --> 01:45:17,892
That hotel, that boat...

1387
01:45:19,020 --> 01:45:22,165
I don't think that's too much to ask.

1388
01:45:26,152 --> 01:45:28,722
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.

1389
01:45:28,822 --> 01:45:31,183
This is just shitty pipe dreams.

1390
01:45:31,283 --> 01:45:33,852
Mexico is way down there
and you're in here...

1391
01:45:33,952 --> 01:45:35,729
...and that's the way it is.

1392
01:45:35,829 --> 01:45:38,665
Yeah, right.
That's the way it is.

1393
01:45:40,166 --> 01:45:42,886
It's down there and I'm in here.

1394
01:45:45,172 --> 01:45:48,657
I guess it comes down to a simple choice.

1395
01:45:50,802 --> 01:45:52,802
Get busy living...

1396
01:45:53,680 --> 01:45:55,682
...or get busy dying.

1397
01:46:07,819 --> 01:46:10,639
If you ever get out of here,
do me a favor.

1398
01:46:10,739 --> 01:46:12,991
Sure, Andy. Anything.

1399
01:46:14,868 --> 01:46:20,107
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

1400
01:46:20,207 --> 01:46:23,443
- A lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

1401
01:46:23,543 --> 01:46:27,614
It's got a long rock wall
with a big oak tree at the north end.

1402
01:46:27,714 --> 01:46:31,410
It's like something
out of a Robert Frost poem.

1403
01:46:31,510 --> 01:46:34,825
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

1404
01:46:35,388 --> 01:46:37,853
We went there for a picnic...

1405
01:46:37,891 --> 01:46:40,585
...and made love under that oak...

1406
01:46:40,685 --> 01:46:43,405
...and I asked and she said yes.

1407
01:46:46,900 --> 01:46:48,900
Promise me, Red.

1408
01:46:49,569 --> 01:46:51,304
If you ever get out...

1409
01:46:51,404 --> 01:46:53,404
...find that spot.

1410
01:46:54,074 --> 01:46:59,980
At the base of that wall, there's a rock
that has no earthly business in Maine.

1411
01:47:00,080 --> 01:47:03,083
Piece of black, volcanic glass.

1412
01:47:05,752 --> 01:47:09,114
Something's buried under it
I want you to have.

1413
01:47:09,214 --> 01:47:10,782
What, Andy?

1414
01:47:10,882 --> 01:47:13,092
What's buried under there?

1415
01:47:14,219 --> 01:47:16,163
You'll have to pry it up...

1416
01:47:16,263 --> 01:47:18,263
...to see.

1417
01:47:23,436 --> 01:47:25,964
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...

1418
01:47:26,064 --> 01:47:28,064
He's talking funny.

1419
01:47:28,900 --> 01:47:30,886
I'm really worried about him.

1420
01:47:30,986 --> 01:47:32,512
Let's keep an eye on him.

1421
01:47:32,612 --> 01:47:37,287
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's all alone.

1422
01:47:37,325 --> 01:47:39,325
Oh, Lord.

1423
01:47:39,786 --> 01:47:41,786
What?

1424
01:47:42,122 --> 01:47:45,025
Andy come down
to the loading dock today.

1425
01:47:45,125 --> 01:47:47,319
He asked me for a length of rope.

1426
01:47:47,419 --> 01:47:48,361
Rope?

1427
01:47:48,461 --> 01:47:50,238
Six feet long.

1428
01:47:50,338 --> 01:47:52,338
And you gave it to him.

1429
01:47:52,591 --> 01:47:54,591
Sure. Why wouldn't I?

1430
01:47:54,593 --> 01:47:56,593
Jesus! Heywood.

1431
01:47:56,761 --> 01:47:58,830
How was I supposed to know?

1432
01:47:58,930 --> 01:48:00,930
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

1433
01:48:02,475 --> 01:48:04,600
Andy would never do that.

1434
01:48:05,020 --> 01:48:07,020
Never.

1435
01:48:08,148 --> 01:48:10,148
I don't know.

1436
01:48:12,319 --> 01:48:15,124
Every man has his breaking point.

1437
01:48:16,698 --> 01:48:19,184
Lickety-split.
Want to get home.

1438
01:48:19,284 --> 01:48:21,409
Just about finished, sir.

1439
01:48:38,178 --> 01:48:40,178
Three deposits tonight.

1440
01:48:47,771 --> 01:48:49,756
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1441
01:48:49,856 --> 01:48:51,591
And shine my shoes.

1442
01:48:51,691 --> 01:48:55,431
- I want them looking like mirrors.
- Yes, sir.

1443
01:49:00,158 --> 01:49:02,368
It's good having you back.

1444
01:49:02,536 --> 01:49:05,426
Place wasn't the same without you.

1445
01:49:51,293 --> 01:49:53,293
Lights out!

1446
01:50:25,202 --> 01:50:28,092
I've had some long nights in stir.

1447
01:50:28,288 --> 01:50:31,024
Alone in the dark
with nothing but your thoughts...

1448
01:50:31,124 --> 01:50:34,014
...time can draw out like a blade.

1449
01:50:39,132 --> 01:50:42,362
That was the longest night of my life.

1450
01:50:57,984 --> 01:50:59,984
Give me a count!

1451
01:51:03,657 --> 01:51:06,493
Tier 3 south, clear!

1452
01:51:09,663 --> 01:51:12,791
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!

1453
01:51:12,999 --> 01:51:14,526
Dufresne!

1454
01:51:14,626 --> 01:51:17,771
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1455
01:51:20,173 --> 01:51:24,933
Don't make me come down
or I'll thump your skull for you!

1456
01:51:31,184 --> 01:51:35,088
Damn it, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

1457
01:51:35,188 --> 01:51:38,592
You'd better be sick or dead in there.
I shit you not!

1458
01:51:38,692 --> 01:51:40,692
You hear me?

1459
01:51:46,157 --> 01:51:48,243
Oh, my Holy God.

1460
01:52:05,218 --> 01:52:08,121
I want every man
on this cellblock questioned.

1461
01:52:08,221 --> 01:52:11,281
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

1462
01:52:13,393 --> 01:52:15,393
Open 237.

1463
01:52:18,440 --> 01:52:22,886
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1464
01:52:22,986 --> 01:52:24,429
Don't tell me that again.

1465
01:52:24,529 --> 01:52:25,680
But sir, he wasn't.

1466
01:52:25,780 --> 01:52:29,242
I can see that, Haig!
Think I'm blind?

1467
01:52:29,910 --> 01:52:31,436
Is that what you're saying?

1468
01:52:31,536 --> 01:52:34,206
- Am I blind, Haig?
- No, sir!

1469
01:52:35,081 --> 01:52:37,584
What about you. You blind?

1470
01:52:38,084 --> 01:52:40,779
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

1471
01:52:40,879 --> 01:52:44,282
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1472
01:52:44,382 --> 01:52:46,382
"Dufresne. "

1473
01:52:47,385 --> 01:52:48,995
He was in his cell...

1474
01:52:49,095 --> 01:52:50,163
...at lights out.

1475
01:52:50,263 --> 01:52:53,458
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.

1476
01:52:53,558 --> 01:52:55,293
I want him found.

1477
01:52:55,393 --> 01:52:58,855
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1478
01:52:59,105 --> 01:53:01,105
Yes, sir.

1479
01:53:01,274 --> 01:53:03,568
Let's go. Move your butts.

1480
01:53:06,947 --> 01:53:08,947
Stand.

1481
01:53:09,407 --> 01:53:11,407
Well?

1482
01:53:13,912 --> 01:53:15,021
Well, what?

1483
01:53:15,121 --> 01:53:19,526
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1484
01:53:19,626 --> 01:53:21,778
He must have said something.

1485
01:53:21,878 --> 01:53:23,697
No, sir, Warden.

1486
01:53:23,797 --> 01:53:25,797
Not a word.

1487
01:53:26,591 --> 01:53:29,135
Lord, it's a miracle!

1488
01:53:29,761 --> 01:53:32,906
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1489
01:53:32,973 --> 01:53:34,973
Nothing left...

1490
01:53:34,975 --> 01:53:37,836
...but some damn rocks on a windowsill.

1491
01:53:37,936 --> 01:53:40,756
And that cupcake on the wall.
Let's ask her.

1492
01:53:40,856 --> 01:53:42,856
Maybe she knows.

1493
01:53:42,858 --> 01:53:47,023
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1494
01:53:47,028 --> 01:53:48,805
Guess not.

1495
01:53:48,905 --> 01:53:51,625
Why should she be any different?

1496
01:53:52,158 --> 01:53:54,158
This is a conspiracy.

1497
01:53:54,494 --> 01:53:56,494
That's what this is.

1498
01:53:56,913 --> 01:54:00,625
One big, damn conspiracy!

1499
01:54:00,917 --> 01:54:02,957
And everyone's in on it!

1500
01:54:03,545 --> 01:54:05,545
Including her!

1501
01:54:39,748 --> 01:54:41,566
In 1966...

1502
01:54:41,666 --> 01:54:44,044
...Andy Dufresne escaped...

1503
01:54:44,252 --> 01:54:46,377
...from Shawshank Prison.

1504
01:54:48,048 --> 01:54:51,159
All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1505
01:54:51,259 --> 01:54:52,911
...a bar of soap...

1506
01:54:53,011 --> 01:54:54,663
...and an old rock hammer...

1507
01:54:54,763 --> 01:54:57,653
...damn near worn down to the nub.

1508
01:55:01,728 --> 01:55:07,050
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years
to tunnel through the wall with it.

1509
01:55:07,150 --> 01:55:09,870
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1510
01:55:28,088 --> 01:55:30,382
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1511
01:55:31,132 --> 01:55:34,619
I imagine it appealed to his
meticulous nature.

1512
01:55:34,719 --> 01:55:36,719
An ice age here...

1513
01:55:36,972 --> 01:55:40,375
...million years of mountain building there.

1514
01:55:40,475 --> 01:55:44,045
Geology is the study of pressure and time.

1515
01:55:44,145 --> 01:55:46,525
That's all it takes, really.

1516
01:55:46,898 --> 01:55:48,508
Pressure...

1517
01:55:48,608 --> 01:55:50,608
...and time.

1518
01:55:51,236 --> 01:55:53,786
That and a big goddamn poster.

1519
01:55:57,325 --> 01:55:58,685
Like I said...

1520
01:55:58,785 --> 01:56:04,055
...in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1521
01:56:05,584 --> 01:56:10,822
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...

1522
01:56:10,922 --> 01:56:12,922
...a handful at a time.

1523
01:56:14,134 --> 01:56:16,328
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1524
01:56:16,428 --> 01:56:19,498
...Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.

1525
01:56:19,598 --> 01:56:22,403
Lickety-split.
I want to get home.

1526
01:56:22,893 --> 01:56:25,358
I'm just about finished, sir.

1527
01:56:46,374 --> 01:56:48,374
Three deposits tonight.

1528
01:56:55,634 --> 01:56:57,928
Andy did like he was told.

1529
01:56:58,136 --> 01:57:01,706
Buffed those shoes to a high mirror-shine.

1530
01:57:05,310 --> 01:57:07,796
The guards simply didn't notice.

1531
01:57:07,896 --> 01:57:09,464
Neither did I.

1532
01:57:09,564 --> 01:57:11,216
I mean, seriously...

1533
01:57:11,316 --> 01:57:15,396
...how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?

1534
01:59:17,859 --> 01:59:21,179
Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...

1535
01:59:21,279 --> 01:59:25,444
...of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.

1536
01:59:25,617 --> 01:59:27,997
Or maybe just don't want to.

1537
01:59:32,332 --> 01:59:34,709
Five hundred yards.

1538
01:59:35,210 --> 01:59:38,780
That's the length of five football fields.

1539
01:59:38,922 --> 01:59:41,466
Just shy of half a mile.

1540
02:00:36,730 --> 02:00:41,510
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...

1541
02:00:41,610 --> 02:00:44,596
...a man nobody ever laid eyes on before...

1542
02:00:44,696 --> 02:00:47,766
...strolled into the Maine National Bank.

1543
02:00:47,866 --> 02:00:51,036
Until that moment,
he didn't exist.

1544
02:00:51,578 --> 02:00:54,272
- Except on paper.
- May I help you?

1545
02:00:54,372 --> 02:00:56,399
He had all the proper ID...

1546
02:00:56,499 --> 02:01:00,529
...driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card...

1547
02:01:00,629 --> 02:01:03,281
And the signature was a spot-on match.

1548
02:01:03,381 --> 02:01:06,576
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1549
02:01:06,676 --> 02:01:09,121
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1550
02:01:09,221 --> 02:01:10,872
Thank you.

1551
02:01:10,972 --> 02:01:12,972
I'm sure I will.

1552
02:01:13,058 --> 02:01:16,503
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1553
02:01:16,603 --> 02:01:18,046
Please.

1554
02:01:18,146 --> 02:01:21,049
Would you add this to your outgoing mail?

1555
02:01:21,149 --> 02:01:23,149
I'd be happy to.

1556
02:01:24,152 --> 02:01:26,152
Good day, sir.

1557
02:01:26,446 --> 02:01:31,226
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

1558
02:01:31,326 --> 02:01:33,019
All told, he blew town...

1559
02:01:33,119 --> 02:01:37,958
...with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

1560
02:01:38,667 --> 02:01:41,419
Severance pay for 19 years.

1561
02:01:48,677 --> 02:01:51,652
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1562
02:02:43,732 --> 02:02:46,843
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1563
02:02:46,943 --> 02:02:51,723
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1564
02:02:51,823 --> 02:02:56,394
I wasn't there to see, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1565
02:02:56,494 --> 02:02:58,789
...when they took him away.

1566
02:03:03,877 --> 02:03:07,702
Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.

1567
02:03:23,104 --> 02:03:24,631
Samuel Norton.

1568
02:03:24,731 --> 02:03:28,386
We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.

1569
02:03:31,905 --> 02:03:33,473
Open the door.

1570
02:03:33,573 --> 02:03:35,573
I'm not sure which key.

1571
02:03:44,960 --> 02:03:47,765
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1572
02:03:58,431 --> 02:04:02,002
I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...

1573
02:04:02,102 --> 02:04:03,795
...other than that bullet...

1574
02:04:03,895 --> 02:04:09,675
...was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1575
02:04:10,819 --> 02:04:14,473
Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...

1576
02:04:14,573 --> 02:04:17,293
...I got a postcard in the mail.

1577
02:04:18,118 --> 02:04:21,021
It was blank,
but the postmark said...

1578
02:04:21,121 --> 02:04:23,248
...Fort Hancock, Texas.

1579
02:04:23,790 --> 02:04:25,358
Fort Hancock...

1580
02:04:25,458 --> 02:04:27,458
...right on the border.

1581
02:04:27,586 --> 02:04:29,796
That's where Andy crossed.

1582
02:04:30,130 --> 02:04:34,534
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...

1583
02:04:34,634 --> 02:04:37,014
...it always makes me laugh.

1584
02:04:38,680 --> 02:04:40,540
Andy Dufresne...

1585
02:04:40,640 --> 02:04:42,751
...who crawled through a river of shit...

1586
02:04:42,851 --> 02:04:46,004
...and came out clean on the other side.

1587
02:04:46,104 --> 02:04:48,104
Andy Dufresne...

1588
02:04:48,273 --> 02:04:50,483
...headed for the Pacific.

1589
02:04:52,819 --> 02:04:55,097
Hadley's got him by the throat, right?

1590
02:04:55,197 --> 02:04:59,101
He says, "I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident. "

1591
02:04:59,201 --> 02:05:02,646
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

1592
02:05:02,746 --> 02:05:04,564
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1593
02:05:04,664 --> 02:05:07,859
"My friends could use a couple of beers. "

1594
02:05:07,959 --> 02:05:09,959
And he got it!

1595
02:05:10,837 --> 02:05:13,407
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1596
02:05:13,507 --> 02:05:15,507
...Andy being gone.

1597
02:05:15,675 --> 02:05:20,163
I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1598
02:05:20,263 --> 02:05:23,238
Their feathers are just too bright.

1599
02:05:24,017 --> 02:05:26,142
And when they fly away...

1600
02:05:26,186 --> 02:05:31,591
...the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1601
02:05:31,691 --> 02:05:33,301
But still...

1602
02:05:33,401 --> 02:05:39,776
...the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.

1603
02:05:41,952 --> 02:05:44,332
I guess just miss my friend.

1604
02:06:09,020 --> 02:06:11,020
Please sit down.

1605
02:06:15,777 --> 02:06:17,777
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1606
02:06:17,904 --> 02:06:21,850
...your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1607
02:06:21,950 --> 02:06:24,925
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1608
02:06:25,954 --> 02:06:27,954
Rehabilitated?

1609
02:06:29,583 --> 02:06:31,583
Well, now, let me see.

1610
02:06:32,460 --> 02:06:35,690
I don't have any idea what that means.

1611
02:06:36,923 --> 02:06:39,659
It means you're ready to rejoin society-

1612
02:06:39,759 --> 02:06:42,989
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1613
02:06:44,264 --> 02:06:46,899
To me it's just a made-up word.

1614
02:06:47,601 --> 02:06:50,151
A politician's word so that...

1615
02:06:50,353 --> 02:06:54,257
...young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1616
02:06:54,357 --> 02:06:56,357
...and have a job.

1617
02:06:57,944 --> 02:07:00,664
What do you really want to know?

1618
02:07:00,780 --> 02:07:02,990
Am I sorry for what I did?

1619
02:07:03,200 --> 02:07:05,200
Well, are you?

1620
02:07:06,286 --> 02:07:10,111
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1621
02:07:10,457 --> 02:07:14,962
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1622
02:07:17,422 --> 02:07:20,482
I look back on the way I was then...

1623
02:07:22,093 --> 02:07:24,093
...a young...

1624
02:07:24,387 --> 02:07:28,382
...stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1625
02:07:30,894 --> 02:07:32,894
I want to talk to him.

1626
02:07:34,523 --> 02:07:37,634
I want to try and talk some sense to him.

1627
02:07:37,734 --> 02:07:40,114
Tell him the way things are.

1628
02:07:41,780 --> 02:07:43,780
But I can't.

1629
02:07:45,408 --> 02:07:47,410
That kid's long gone...

1630
02:07:48,620 --> 02:07:51,935
...and this old man is all that's left.

1631
02:07:52,791 --> 02:07:54,831
I got to live with that.

1632
02:07:55,627 --> 02:07:57,627
Rehabilitated?

1633
02:07:57,671 --> 02:07:59,881
It's just a bullshit word.

1634
02:08:00,465 --> 02:08:06,075
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1635
02:08:06,471 --> 02:08:08,957
Because to tell you the truth...

1636
02:08:09,057 --> 02:08:11,059
...I don't give a shit.

1637
02:09:37,604 --> 02:09:39,604
Here you go, miss.

1638
02:09:41,942 --> 02:09:43,942
Restroom break?

1639
02:09:48,782 --> 02:09:54,817
You don't need to ask me every time
you need to go take a piss. Just go.

1640
02:10:06,341 --> 02:10:10,162
Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.

1641
02:10:10,262 --> 02:10:13,492
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1642
02:10:16,768 --> 02:10:19,318
There's a harsh truth to face.

1643
02:10:20,605 --> 02:10:24,260
No way I'm going to make it on the outside.

1644
02:10:31,366 --> 02:10:35,771
All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...

1645
02:10:35,871 --> 02:10:38,591
...so maybe they'd send me back.

1646
02:10:43,545 --> 02:10:46,265
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1647
02:10:46,882 --> 02:10:48,658
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1648
02:10:48,758 --> 02:10:50,758
Knew it all too well.

1649
02:10:52,304 --> 02:10:56,041
All I want is to be back
where things make sense.

1650
02:10:56,141 --> 02:10:59,966
Where I won't have to be afraid all the time.

1651
02:11:00,854 --> 02:11:03,231
Only one thing stops me.

1652
02:11:04,649 --> 02:11:07,068
A promise I made to Andy.

1653
02:11:27,589 --> 02:11:29,589
There it is.

1654
02:11:39,351 --> 02:11:41,351
Much obliged, sir.

1655
02:15:20,322 --> 02:15:21,723
Dear Red:

1656
02:15:21,823 --> 02:15:24,392
If you're reading this,
you've gotten out...

1657
02:15:24,492 --> 02:15:28,730
...and if you've come this far,
maybe you'd come a bit further.

1658
02:15:28,830 --> 02:15:32,570
You remember the name
of the town, don't you?

1659
02:15:33,585 --> 02:15:35,585
Zihuatanejo.

1660
02:15:36,755 --> 02:15:40,742
I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.

1661
02:15:40,842 --> 02:15:45,080
I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.

1662
02:15:45,180 --> 02:15:46,832
Remember, Red...

1663
02:15:46,932 --> 02:15:49,142
...hope is a good thing...

1664
02:15:49,226 --> 02:15:51,336
...maybe the best of things.

1665
02:15:51,436 --> 02:15:53,816
And no good thing ever dies.

1666
02:15:54,105 --> 02:15:57,092
I will be hoping that this letter finds you...

1667
02:15:57,192 --> 02:15:59,192
...and finds you well.

1668
02:15:59,444 --> 02:16:00,762
Your friend...

1669
02:16:00,862 --> 02:16:02,862
...Andy.

1670
02:16:35,856 --> 02:16:37,716
"Get busy living...

1671
02:16:37,816 --> 02:16:39,816
...or get busy dying. "

1672
02:16:42,404 --> 02:16:44,573
That's goddamn right.

1673
02:16:49,828 --> 02:16:52,063
For the second time in my life...

1674
02:16:52,163 --> 02:16:55,223
...I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1675
02:16:55,834 --> 02:16:57,834
Parole violation.

1676
02:16:58,420 --> 02:17:02,657
Of course I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

1677
02:17:02,757 --> 02:17:04,910
Not for an old crook like me.

1678
02:17:05,010 --> 02:17:07,390
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1679
02:17:10,682 --> 02:17:15,754
I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1680
02:17:15,854 --> 02:17:19,299
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

1681
02:17:19,399 --> 02:17:22,010
A free man at the start of a long journey...

1682
02:17:22,110 --> 02:17:24,915
...whose conclusion is uncertain.

1683
02:17:27,699 --> 02:17:31,014
I hope I can make it across the border.

1684
02:17:31,870 --> 02:17:35,525
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.

1685
02:17:36,791 --> 02:17:41,636
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

1686
02:17:42,714 --> 02:17:44,714
I hope.


